	<div class="col-md-8">

		<p>Paul Bogard is the Lead Engineer for KC-46 Aircrew Training Systems with the United States Air Force at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio. He has been performing acquisition of full flight simulators as a systems engineer since 2009.  He holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering from <%= link_to("Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology",'http://www.rose-hulman.edu/') %> and a Master of Science in Computer Engineering from <%= link_to("Wright State University",'http://www.wright.edu/') %>.</p>

		<p>Paul enjoys travel, airports, airplanes, trains, interesting roads and intersections, and nearly anything else related to transportation. He currently lives in Beavercreek, Ohio.</p>

